      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>A chemist requires a large amount of 1-bromo-2-pentene as starting material for a synthesis and decides to carry out an NBS allylic bromination reaction. What is wrong with the following synthesis plan? What side products would form in addition to the desired product?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBanNUIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--52484729a386103dae4d4480a212d4eefba464a2/OChem_10_EC_021.jpg\" alt=\"Pent-2-ene reacts with N-bromosuccinimide, light, and carbon tetrachloride to form 1-bromopent-2-ene.\">",
